				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Lookin to Twink a bard!<a name="28010"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 16 04 8:05 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Depends on how much you have to spend. My suggestions:
<br />

<br />
-Make sure your deity is Rallos Zek
<br />
Chest: Architect’s Bejeweled Chestplate
<br />
Legs: Fierce Heraldic Grieves
<br />
Boots: Fierce Heraldic Boots
<br />
Back: Crinose Cape of the Werewolf
<br />
Shoulders: Fierce Heraldic Pauldrons
<br />
Arms: Fierce Heraldic Vambraces
<br />
Wrist: Fierce Heraldic Bracer x2
<br />
Gloves: Fierce Heraldic Gauntlets
<br />
Waist: Soulscream Belt (note, haste was nerfed due to recommended level, so don't expect 31% haste before the recommended level cap goes away)
<br />
Rings: Tear Shaped Ring (If you can find it), Velium Fire Wedding Ring (then upgrade to Valorium Ring of Gallantry once 46)
<br />
Ears: Black Sapphire Electrum Earring x2
<br />
Helm: Fierce Heraldic Helm
<br />
Face: Fierce Heraldic Visor
<br />
Range: Goranga Idol
<br />

<br />
Instruments/Weapons:
<br />
Percussion: Thunderous Drums of Karana or Battle Drummer's Main-Gauche
<br />

<br />
Stringed: Combine Lute (Will not stack with Tear Shaped Ring)
<br />

<br />
Brass: Troubadour’s Mace
<br />

<br />
Wind: Wooden Flute 
<br />
-------
<br />
Basic Starting Guide.
<br />

<br />
Steamfont newbie grounds are arguably the best place to level until 7. 
<br />

<br />
Get a cheap weapon with no recommended level on it and just level to 7 with melee.
<br />

<br />
1-3 Steamfont Newbie Mobs (rats, spiders, little gnome skeletons. Runaway Clockworks, Puma's or Coyote's if you're feeling frisky)
<br />

<br />
3-7 Bind yourself in PoK at the soulbinder. Kill what you can in the Kobold camps until you die. You will respawn in PoK with full health and your entire armor. Run and zone back into Steamfont. Repeat until level 7. Loot all the Teeth and Pelts, you can make an easy 50pp off of these by the time you reach 7 by just selling them to a merchant.  
<br />

<br />
7-9 Field of Bone, &quot;The Pit&quot;. Kill whatever's roaming around. Again just kill until you die and run back. 
<br />

<br />
9-12 Kurn's Tower. Outside of Field of Bone you'll see a huge tower. There are skeletons here that are easy kills and amazing exp. They are also quite plentiful. Try and get a group if possible. It shouldn't be much of a problem considering lots like to PL/level there.  
<br />

<br />
12-17. Unrest. Learn to AE kite (Their are guides in the solo section of this forum). You will do 12 to 17 in a matter of hours once you get the hang of AE kiting. 
<br />

<br />
17-24. Paludral Caverns. I hate this zone, but honestly it's the quickest way to get to 24. Learn to pull for groups using your level 8 lull song. 
<br />

<br />
24-36+. Iceclad Ocean. AE kite cougar's, (there is a guide in the solo section of the forum). It's a bit tough at first considering you're not on flat ground. The levels will fly by though. Usually uncamped.
<br />

<br />
I'm still unsure of where to go at this point myself. I've been doing LDoN lately. Pretty easy to find a group as a Bard. Learn to pull via lull song.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
