			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Lookin to Twink a bard!<a name="28021"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 16 04 8:44 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I wouldn't worry about twinking a bard as long as you intend to play the character along the way.   High AC and HP at an early level simply means that you may not develop some of our escape techniques until later in your bardic career as you can stand toe to toe with most old world mobs for quite some time.
<br />

<br />
I'd twink in essentially two stages.  At stage one, the early levels, I'd go for the top items with AC/HP with no reduction in stats for level (e.g., flayed barbarian hide mask, flayed barbarian skin leggings, barbed ringmail, etc.) and good instruments.
<br />

<br />
At stage two, somewhere in the late 40s or early 50s, switch to the best gear available for the platinum with a concentration on mana regeneration as well.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
