				<td colspan="2"><span>I would have to say that I am against twinking any char.....to an  extent.  I set myself with a limit.  I won't spend more than 2k on an alt.  until it's 30+ then not more than an additional 10k til 50+  when I'll get whatever is good for the money.  I find that I learn to play the class a lil easier than others because I have to watch every aspect a lil closer.  I think that the ease with which I learn to play alts also comes a lil from having a bard for my main and first char.  I haven't found another char yet that can match the intricacies and the determination required to play a bard.  you will hate low levels.....low levels with a bard just suck....no getting around it.  you REALLY learn to play your bard after you get selo's 2.5 and 4 chants.  by this time you've been grouping a bit...understand it....but now it's your time to shine...go solo a bit.  if you can learn to kite 20ish mobs to the ground groups are cake.  once I learned how to play my bard groups are so easy that I generally ML Pull CC and twist 3-4 songs for my ldon groups.  that didn't come until after it was life or death for myself learning to TWIST 4 songs to kite mobs to death.  it's also better to learn to twist solo than in a group because if you screw up....you die....not the 5 people with you<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
